{{short description|Information rate that can be transmitted over a given bandwidth}}
{{Use American English|date=December 2022}}

Spectral efficiency, spectrum efficiency or bandwidth efficiency refers to the [[information rate]] that can be transmitted over a given [[Bandwidth (signal processing)|bandwidth]] in a specific communication system. It is a measure of how efficiently a limited frequency spectrum is utilized by the [[physical layer]] protocol, and sometimes by the [[medium access control]] (the [[channel access]] protocol).<ref name=Miao>[[Guowang Miao]], Jens Zander, Ki Won Sung, and Ben Slimane, Fundamentals of Mobile Data Networks, Cambridge University Press, {{ISBN|1107143217}}, 2016.</ref>
